Regarding the bonus question, calculating the intersection between a ray and a plane/sphere/triangle is a common problem in computer graphics. There are many algorithms to solve this problem, but one common approach is to use the parametric equation of a line to represent the ray and the implicit equation of the surface to represent the plane/sphere/triangle. The intersection point can then be found by solving the resulting system of equations.

